uk.ac.ebi.gxa.netcdf.generator
Interface NetCDFGenerator

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultNetCDFGenerator
public interface NetCDFGenerator

Interface for building a NetCDFs, as required by the Atlas expression analytics. Implementations should provide a way of setting the NetCDF repository location, which may be of a generic type to allow the NetCDFs to be built into a repository backed by a database, file system, or some other datasource. Any implementation should implement generateNetCDFs() which contains the logic to construct the NetCDF repository.

Author:
Tony Burdett

generateNetCDFs

void generateNetCDFs()
Run the NetCDFGenerator as a standalone, complete mechanism to generate all possible NetCDFs. If you wish to only regenerate a small slice of data, use generateNetCDFsForExperiment(String).

Note that this method is not guaranteed to be synchronous, it only guarantees that the generation of NetCDFs has started. Implementations are free to define their own multithreaded strategies for NetCDF generation. If you wish to be notified on completion, you should register a listener to get callback events when the build completes by using generateNetCDFs(uk.ac.ebi.gxa.netcdf.generator.listener.NetCDFGeneratorListener). You can also use a listener to get at any errors that may have occurred during NetCDF generation.

Calling this method is equivalent to calling generateNetCDFs(null).

generateNetCDFsForExperiment

void generateNetCDFsForExperiment(String experimentAccession)
Run the NetCDFGenerator to regenerate NetCDFs for only one particular accession.

Note that this method is not guaranteed to be synchronous, it only guarantees that the generation of NetCDFs has started. Implementations are free to define their own multithreaded strategies for NetCDF generation. If you wish to be notified on completion, you should register a listener to get callback events when the build completes by using generateNetCDFsForExperiment(String, uk.ac.ebi.gxa.netcdf.generator.listener.NetCDFGeneratorListener). You can also use a listener to get at any errors that may have occurred during NetCDF generation.

Calling this method is equivalent to calling generateNetCDFsForExperiment(experimentAccession, null).

Parameters:
experimentAccession - the accession of the experiment to generate
